Let me say this first.  I am NOT a WoW fanboi.  I just wanted to point out the core difference between D2 and WoW.  D2 was free to play and it could be played by connecting to your buddy's pc and having your own private little game.  This was why D2 was soo hacktastic.  When the end user controls both the client and the server, anything can happen.
<br />

<br />
WoW is going to be a subscription based MMOG where the only way the end user can play is to connect to servers run and monitored by Blizzard, <span style="font-style: italic">just like everquest</span>.  Guess what?  That means that WoW will have paid GMs, CS and staff programmers dedicated to solving bugs/hacks and developing new content funded by user subscriptions, <span style="font-style: italic">just like everquest</span>!
<br />

<br />
Having secure server software that is not released to the public is infinitely more secure than the D2 method.
<br />

<br />
Yes, there will be cheating in WoW.  But guess what?  It's going to be just like the cheating you see in EQ, nothing more and probably less.  Chances are, with Blizzard knowing what kind of problems and hacks that EQ has had to fight, they will probably be able to weaken or eliminate some things that EQ can simply not combat because it would require a complete rewrite of the game.
<br />

<br />
That's what FFXI did.  Their game was designed to make any kind of "ShowFFXI" that might ever be created practically useless(mob info is not sent to the client until the player gets within a certain range, which is usually about visual range).
<br />

<br />
Personally, I don't know whether i will play WoW when it comes out.  I suppose that will largely depend on how happy I am with my character, my class or eq in general when that day comes.
<br />
 
<br />
I am <span style="font-weight: bold">not</span> just biding time waiting for another game to come out.  I play EQ because I enjoy it.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=583843&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Decimous</a> 65 Arch Convoker
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=181735" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ceknor</a> 57 Preserver
<br />
Bertoxxulous
<br />
